 monumental heritage in the context of large public performances and civic spectacles of great emotional impact. The first part of the volume focuses on the sites of Carchemish and Zincirli, offering a close reading of the relevant archaeological contexts. The second part of the volume discusses the embedment of monumental art in ritual performance and examines how change in art relates to change in ceremonial behavior, and how the latter relates in turn to change in power structures and models of rulership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHittitesxCivilization. 0aMonumentszTurkeyzCarchemish (Extinct city) 0aMonumentszTurkeyzCarchemish (Extinct city). 0aMonumentszTurkeyzZincirli (Gaziantep İli) 0aMonumentszTurkeyzZincirli (Gaziantep İli). 0aRelief (Sculpture), HittitezTurkeyzCarchemish (Extinct city) 0aRelief (Sculpture), HittitezTurkeyzCarchemish (Extinct city). 0aRelief (Sculpture), HittitezTurkeyzZincirli (Gaziantep İli) 0aRelief (Sculpture), HittitezTurkeyzZincirli (Gaziantep İli). 4aAssyrien. 4aHethiter. 4aMesopotamien. 4aVisuelle Kommunikation. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aArcheology of Crowds, Visual Communication.  aAssyria.  aHittites.  aMesopotamia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311022225840uh